title: Price Over Earnings Overview: Travelzoo

Shares of several companies in the travel, casino and lodging space are trading lower as markets dip following US jobless claims and consumer spending data. The coronavirus pandemic has reduced travel and lodging demand. Casino stocks may also be reacting following statements from NV governor suggesting casinos may not reopen until the later phases of the reopening process.

Shares of several travel, lodging and leisure companies are trading higher following positive data from a study of Gilead's Remdesivir. This has raised optimism towards a potential coronavirus treatment, which could mean a sooner return to travel.

Shares of several companies in the travel and lodging/resort spaces are trading lower as markets dip on a decline in oil prices. A drop in oil prices has raised concerns over the economic impact of the coronavirus pandemic, which has hurt the travel space
